      {
        "content": "Reentrancy-class drain via ERC677 transferAndCall hook\n\nBug-bounty disclosure: a lending market accepted a token implementing transferAndCall; the hook re-entered the borrow flow before collateral state was finalized, enabling an over-borrow. Root cause is the same checks-effects-interactions violation as classic reentrancy but triggered by a non-standard token callback. Mitigation: nonReentrant on all state-touching entrypoints and finalize accounting before external token movement.",
        "doc_id": "immunefi-reentrancy-cream-2021",
        "chunk_id": 0,
        "total_chunks": 1,
